Covid-19 super-spreader events have become the norm, and will surely continue into the New Year.Year 2021 is bound to be a political one that diverts us all from the far more urgent tasks of mere survival. We usually approach a new year full of hope and optimism. Even with the ‘annus horribilis’ of 2020, we should be confident that having scraped the bottom, we can only look up to good tidings.
There is little to indicate that 2021 heralds better things. Covid-19 made this a lost year, and even with vaccine promises, there is little to indicate that we are anywhere near to overcoming devastation wrought by the worst global pandemic in over 100 years.



