Year 2021 is bound to be a political one that diverts us all from the far more urgent tasks of mere survival. The tragedy is that then when the economic and political elite fight for their slices of Kenya, all the rest of us are drawn into these greedy battles.
The Uhuru-Ruto partnership was not about Kenya but about two incompatible individuals entering a marriage of convenience. It follows that the divorce should not concern us at all, and neither should Mr Kenyatta’s dalliance with opposition chieftain Raila Odinga.
The extent to which we get sucked into selfish political battles is perfectly illustrated by a video in wide circulation featuring former Starehe MP, ‘Bishop Dr’ Margaret Wanjiru, and her bid for the office of Nairobi Governor left vacant with impeachment of the mercurial Mike Mbuvi Sonko.
Like all politicians with problems standing on their own two feet, the prosperity gospel evangelist must seek the crutch of a dominant political player; in this case DP Ruto, who is engaged in a titanic battle against President Kenyatta and Mr Odinga.





She chooses to stake her claim by asserting that the Uhuru-Ruto ‘kumi-kumi’ power transfer pact is binding to all the Kikuyu people. Total and absolute rubbish! If there was such an agreement, it was between two individuals. I was not consulted and I’m not aware of any member of my immediate and extended family who was.



